From: =?UTF-8?q?Bartek=20Iwa=C5=84czuk?= <biwanczuk@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 16:43:01 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] fix: use MAX_STRING_LENGTH instead of MAX_LENGTH in
 string_decoder

MAX_LENGTH is the max Buffer size (Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER), while
MAX_STRING_LENGTH is the V8 string length limit (~537M). The original
code imported MAX_STRING_LENGTH from node:buffer constants.
---
 ext/node/polyfills/string_decoder.ts | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

